CatDescriptText: Evelyn Williams, nurse, 2338 Bedford Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe that city patrolmen and firemen should be required to work more than 40 hours per week?" answer reads: "Yes, they should, but also they should get paid..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Evelyn Williams wearing dark dress and light colored cropped cardigan, standing with hands on hips, in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
